{"reasoning":"The bug is that feature flags are stored and expected in snake_case, but some callers use camelCase names. The existing lookup used dict.get() with a default of False, which makes missing keys indistinguishable from disabled flags and silently hides naming mismatches. I refactored the module to normalize incoming flag names from camelCase/PascalCase to snake_case before lookup, while keeping the public flag listing unchanged. This preserves existing behavior for valid snake_case keys and makes mixed-case callers work correctly without changing the flag storage format.","files":{"code_snippets_v2/silent_default_a/flags.py":""""Feature flag system with snake_case keys."""

FLAGS = {
